Police are hunting a one-eared man after a brutal assault which left another man with his ear hanging off.

Metropolitan Police officers are trying to track 25-year-old Anthony Kenny, who is missing his left ear, in connection with the attack.

A man was reportedly slashed in the face in the early hours of Saturday morning, in Stoke Newington, north London.

Police are hunting one-eared Anthony Kenny after an assault in which another man's ear was injured

The victim was left with several facial injuries and is understood to have been taken to hospital after suffering damage to his ear.

Kenny, of Islington, is described as white and has 'Stand alone' tattooed on his neck and 'North London' permanently inked on his left hand.

The suspect is said to have links with Islington in north London, Chelmsford in Essex, and St Albans, Hertfordshire.

Detectives have told members of the public not approach Kenny, but to call 999 if they see him.

Anyone with information about the incident is asked to contact Islington CID on 07766 781861 or call Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111.

The attack happened in the Green Lanes, Stoke Newington. Police are appealing for information

 

